TITLE:
      Rapid Opiate Detoxification and Naltrexone Induction Using Buprenorphine - 2
SUMMARY:
      The purpose of this study is to develop a clinical protocol to detoxify patients from
      opiates to naltrexone using buprenorphine and to develop pilot data for a grant application
      for a controlled study of the efficacy of the new clinical protocol for outpatients.
ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA:
      Inclusion Criteria:

        Males/Females, ages 21-50. Opiate dependence according to DSM-IV criteria. Self-reported
        use within the last 30 days. Agreeable to conditions of study and signed informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        psychiatric disorder that requires medication therapy. History of seizures. Pregnant
        and/or nursing women. Dependent on etoh or benzodiazepines or other sedative-hypnotics.
        Acute hepatitis. Other medical conditions that deem participation to be unsafe.
